<HEADLINE> Iran Condemns Israeli Air Raids on Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Ministry
spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi on Friday condemned the Israeli
attacks on Lebanon that caused death and injuries of civilians
over the past few days.
</P>
<P>
Asefi said that the attacks represented the belligerent and
aggressive spirit of the Israeli regime in the region, the
Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Israel launched large-scale air strikes on Lebanon since
Thursday night to avenge the Katyusha rocket attacks on its
northern areas by the Lebanese Hezbollah guerrillas Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At least eight people have reportedly been killed and 60
others injured in the attacks. Deploring the death and injury
of innocent civilians in Lebanon, he said that the powers
which supply Israel with the latest in armament are also
responsible for those crimes.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also called on the Muslim nations and
responsible international authorities to pressurize Israel to
abandon criminal perpetration in the future.
</P>
<P>
The recent blitz bombings on Lebanon were also evidence
that the Israeli regime is not committed even to the
documents and pledges that it has signed, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
