<HEADLINE> Arab League Demands End to Israeli Aggression on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League on Friday demanded
an immediate end to the Israeli "heinous aggression" on Lebanon
and its "repression policy."
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the latest Israeli air raid on Lebanese civilian
targets, Arab League Assistant Secretary-General Ahmed Ben Hulai
accused Israel of violating and challenging international law by
attacking civilian facilities in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The 22-nation pan-Arab forum "follows with great concern" the
constant Israeli assaults on Lebanese lands, which claim the lives
of innocent people, Ben Hulai said.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation for rocket attacks by Lebanese guerrillas on
Israel's northern areas, the Jewish state launched air strikes
Thursday night against power stations, water plants and roads near
the Lebanese capital, Beirut, leaving at least eight people dead
and more than 60 others injured.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League official said the league supports all
international efforts aimed at stopping the Israeli aggression
which jeopardizes the security and stability in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ben Hulai underlined that Israel's aggression and
repression policy has been proved repeatedly to be a failure in
face of the steadfastness of the Lebanese people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
