<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrea Alleges Ethiopia Launches Fresh Attack on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia Friday morning opened a
new attack on the right flank of the Mereb-Setit front, the
Eritrean Foreign Ministry claimed in a press released reaching
here Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
"The attack started around 8:00 a.m. (local time) this
morning," the release said, adding that "Fighting was going on at
2:00 p.m., the press time."
</P>
<P>
The Eritrean Foreign Ministry noted that the Ethiopian fresh
attack on the Mereb-Setit front was in the wake of U.N. Security
Council demand Wednesday for immediate and unconditional
cease-fire between the two Horn of African nations.
</P>
<P>
From June 10 to 16, the two countries were confronted in border
battles along the central flank of the same front.
</P>
<P>
Eritrea said its forces killed or wounded more than 18,000
Ethiopian soldiers during the week-long fighting and also
destroyed four Mig-23 fighter planes and a helicopter gun ship.
</P>
<P>
While Ethiopia claimed that its troops had put 21,000 Eritrean
soldiers out of action in the border battles.
</P>
<P>
War between Ethiopia and Eritrea broke out in early May 1998
along the 1, 000-kilometer border.
</P>
<P>
Although both countries have agreed to the peace framework put
forward by the Organization of African Unity (OAU), there is no
sight for immediate resolution to the 13-month-long conflict.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
