<HEADLINE> Rwanda Hails Trial of Catholic Priest in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan government welcomed
the decision by France to try Rwandan Catholic priest, Father
Wenceslas Munyeshyaka, Rwanda's Chief Prosecutor, Simeon Rwagasore
said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The prosecutor said more than 45 genocide survivors, both Hutus
and Tutsis, testified about Munyeshyaka's role in the massacres of
Tutsis at Sainte Famille church, in the heart of the capital
Kigali during April-July 1994, the Rwanda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"France appointed a prosecutor to follow up his case and has
ordered him to appear before the court," Rwagasore said.
</P>
<P>
Many human rights organizations have accused France, the
Vatican, Belgium and other Western countries for harboring
genocide suspects.
</P>
<P>
In April 1995, at the eve of the fifth commemoration of the
1994 genocide the London-based human rights Watchdog, African
Rights published a report on Munyeshyaka's role in the killings at
Sainte Famille.
</P>
<P>
"However, the French government had kept silent about his
case," African Rights charged.
</P>
<P>
"Over a period of three months Munyeshyaka is said to have
collaborated with the militia in sending Tutsis to be
slaughtered, the majority of them young men,'' it said in the
report.
</P>
<P>
Munyeshyaka is also charged with raping young women, whom he
saved in return for sexual favors, and of depriving the majority
of refugees of water and food.
</P>
<P>
The report further said that Munyeshyaka was seen around by the
 displaced armed with a gun, and wearing a bullet proof jacket. He
had turned himself into a militiaman, the report said.
</P>
<P>
African Rights also accused Munyeshyaka of obstructed the
evacuation of the refugees by the UN peace-keepers.
</P>
<P>
After the genocide, Munyeshyaka fled to eastern part of former
Zaire where he was fished out and taken to France where continues
to celebrate mass.
</P>
<P>
All these allegations were rejected by Munyeshyaka calling them
'' malicious gossips'' intended to tarnish his reputation and that
of the Catholic Church.
</P>
<P>
African Rights alleged that all attempt to bring Munyeshyaka to
book were curtailed by intervention of the French Catholic leaders
who had dismissed charges against him.
</P>
<P>
If Munyeshyaka happens to be tried in France, he will be the
second Rwandan genocide suspect to be tried in a European country,
after the trial of Fulgence Niyonteze who was sentenced to life
imprisonment by a Swiss military court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0028 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia to Shoot Film in Space </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Russia, the first country to be in
space, plans to make another first in space, this time by shooting
a feature film there.
</P>
<P>
An actor and two cosmonauts to act as cameramen will be sent up
to the Mir space station in February 2000, Sergei Gorbunov, press
secretary for the director general of the Russian Space Agency,
told a press conference Friday.
</P>
<P>
Director Yuri Kara, meanwhile, will stay at the mission control
center and direct the filming from there, the Interfax news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
"Nobody has filmed actors in space yet," Kara said. "Even if we
shoot just one frame in space we will be the first to do so."
</P>
<P>
Only part of the film, based on the novel "Cassandra's Brand"
by Kyrgyz writer Chingiz Aitmatov and tentatively named as "A
Prize Space Mission," will be shot in space.
</P>
<P>
In Aitmatov's story, the last cosmonaut on board a space
station slotted for destruction refuses to abandon it.
</P>
<P>
Actor Vladimir Steklov, who will star in the film, is
undergoing a full 900-hour training regime for his space flight,
as is Natalya Khromushkina, a young actress who will play the part
of the cosmonaut's girlfriend.
</P>
<P>
Footage of her will be filmed either on earth or in a dropping
transport plane to simulate weightlessness. She is undergoing
training for space missions just in case Steklov cannot fly.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
