<HEADLINE> U.S. Says American Detain in DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. State Department on
Friday confirmed that an American was arrested in the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) on a charge of "violations of
law."
</P>
<P>
"The government of the DPRK has confirmed to Swedish
authorities that an American citizen was arrested on June 17,"
State Department spokesman James Rubin told reporters.
</P>
<P>
The individual -- whose name was not mentioned -- "is being
investigated for alleged violations of law," he said.
</P>
<P>
He declined to provide more details, only saying he was
prevented from doing so because of U.S. privacy laws.
</P>
<P>
The United States is urging the DPRK to provide Swedish
diplomats with quick and early consular access to the detained
American citizen.
</P>
<P>
The United States has no formal diplomatic relations with the
DPRK and depends on Sweden to represent its interests in
Pyongyang. 
</P>
