<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets in Mixed Mode </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON June 25 (Xinhua) - British and German stocks held on to
modest gains Friday to close slightly higher following a strong
opening on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
London had suffered at the outset, weighed down by Wall
Street's 132-point overnight fall, a lack of corporate trading
news and caution ahead of next week's US Federal Reserve policy
meeting.
</P>
<P>
However, the UK's benchmark FTSE 100 overcame early losses to
close up 0.3 percent, or 18.7 percent, at 6435.4, pulled higher by
a firmer performance on the Dow Jones industrial average.
</P>
<P>
Germany's electronically traded Xetra Dax also climbed out the
red to end 0.24 percent higher, at 5340.63, a gain of 13.03
points.
</P>
<P>
But Deutsche Telekom shares fell 1.65 percent as investors
attempted to drive its share price down ahead of a giant new share
issue.
</P>
<P>
In Paris, the blue chip CAC 40 gave up 0.4 percent to finish at
4415.47, uninspired by a stronger start on Wall Street.  
