<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1430 GMT, June 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Britain and other members of the European Union are
ready to offer assistance to the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC)
as soon as a cease-fire agreement is signed.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail newspaper Saturday quoted Diane Mckelvey,
second secretary at the British High Commission in Lusaka, as
saying: "the British government, European Union and others stand
ready to offer assistance to the people of the DRC as soon as
there is a cease-fire there that makes that possible." (EU-DRC-Aid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- The United Nations Secretary General's special envoy
for East Timor, Jamsheed Marker, left Dili, the capital of East
Timor, on Saturday for Jakarta after ending a three-day visit to
the territory.
</P>
<P>
"I believe the Indonesian government, the military and the
police have a good intention to settle the East Timor case through
the direct ballot, as stated in the May 5 agreement," Marker said
before boarding a commercial plane at Dili's Comoro airport. (
Indonesia-UN-E.Timor)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein has denounced the
air raids by Israeli forces on civilian targets in Lebanon as acts
perpetrated by "forces of extremism" in the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
During his telephone conversations with Syrian President Hafez
al-Assad and Lebanese President Emile Lahoud Friday night,
Abdullah denounced the Israeli air raids as "a flagrant violent
violation" of the April 1996 agreement to ban attacks on civilian
targets.
</P>
<P>
The king reiterated Jordan's absolute support for Lebanon and
total condemnation of the attacks targeted innocent civilians and
infrastructure installations, which could build up tensions in the
region. (Jordan-Israel-Condemnations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- A Russian military transport plane with an advance
unit of paratroopers left for Pristina's Slatina airport Saturday,
the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The plane was to depart at 10:00 local time (08:00 GMT), but
the take-off was delayed by arrangements of air corridors in
Europe, Itar-Tass said without elaboration.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft carries 21 paratroopers, 18 air force specialists
and technical equipment. (Russia-Kosovo-Peacekeepers) 
</P>
</TEXT>
