<HEADLINE> Becker, Agassi Enters Fourth Round at Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- German Boris Becker and American
Andre Agass entered the fourth round after defeating their
respective rivals at the Wimbledon tennis championships on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Becker edged Australian Lleyton Hewitt 6-1, 6-4, 7-6 (7-5) and
fourth seed Agassi eliminated Alberto Martin of Spain 6-2, 6-0, 2-
6, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The unseeded Becker, who plans to retire this summer, turned in
his second successive strong showing on Center Court. He served
well, dominated at the net and overpowered young rising star
Hewitt.
</P>
<P>
31-year-old Becker, a three-time Wimbledon champion, advanced
to the round of 16 for the 12th time.
</P>
<P>
American amateur Alexandra Stevenson, an 18-year-old qualifier,
ousted 11th-seeded Julie Halard-Decugis 0f France 6-3, 6-3 in the
women's third round.
</P>
<P>
Her compatriot Lindsay Davenport, third seed, overwhelmed
Italian Laura Golarsa 6-3, 6-2. Ninth seed Mary Pierce of France
beat German Elena Wager 6-3, 6-0.
</P>
<P>
1997 French Open champion Gustavo Kuerten became the first
Brazilian man to reach Wimbledon's fourth round in the Open era,
which began in 1968. The 11th-seeded Kuerten, swept past
qualifier Nenad Zimonjic of Yugoslavia 6-4, 6-4, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
