<HEADLINE> Qatar Condemns Israeli Attacks Against Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Qatar on Saturday condemned
Israel's air raids on Lebanon and called for an
unconditional withdrawal of Israeli troops from southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli aggression is a "flagrant threat to the sovereignty
and security of Lebanon," said Qatari Foreign Minister Sheikh
Hamad Bin Jassim al-Thani.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamad called on the world community to intervene
immediately to end the aggression, the Kuwait News Agency reported
from Doha, capital of Qatar.
</P>
<P>
He also urged Israel to implement the United Nations Security
Council resolution which called for an unconditional Israeli
withdrawal from the occupied Lebanese territories.
</P>
<P>
Israel warplanes, in the past two days, launched heavy air
strikes against Lebanese infrastructure and civilian areas,
killing at least eight people and wounded 60 others. 
</P>
