<HEADLINE> Nanjing Hosts Int'l Symposium On Community Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- An International Symposium on
Community Service and Development opened here today, with more
than 100 experts attending.
</P>
<P>
Experts from China, Canada, the Republic of Korea, Japan,
Australia, Denmark, the United States, and Hong Kong and Taiwan
regions will conduct a comparative study of communities in China
and other countries, and discuss an applicable format for Chinese
community service.
</P>
<P>
They will also study issues like promoting the development of
worldwide community service and offer various schemes during the
two-day seminar.
</P>
<P>
Participants visited a Nanjing community center this morning,
whose quality service won applause from the international experts.
</P>
<P>
Promoting the development of community service in China is one
of the demands of urban modernization and an urgent requirement
for urban dwellers who wish to improve the quality of their lives.
China will continue to improve the management of community service,
said Yang Yanyin, Chinese vice minister of civil affairs, at today
's meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
