<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Drives Highway Through Qinling Range </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Lantian-Xiaoshangyuan Highway,
the first highway in northwest China's Shaanxi Province that goes
through the Qinling mountain range, which is the meteorological
watershed between northern and southern China, was opened to
traffic today.
</P>
<P>
The 48.5-km-long highway, part of the 312 National Highway from
Shanghai to Yining in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, is a
second-grade road exclusively for the use of motor vehicles. Its
total cost was 364 million yuan (about 44 million US dollars),
including a World Bank loan of 16 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The highway is from 7-9 m wide. It has six tunnels with a total
length of 2.28 km and 46 bridges with a total length of 2.2 km,
and has designed speeds of 40 kph in the mountains and 80 kph on
the plain.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
