<HEADLINE> '99 Changbai Mountains Forest Tourism Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The '99 Changbai Mountains
Forest Tourism Festival Opened today in northeast China's Jilin
Province.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Administration Bureau of the Changbai
Mountains Nature Reserve, the festival aims to show the mountains'
abundant natural resources, cultivate awareness of environmental
protection among the general public and achieve the harmony of
man and nature.
</P>
<P>
Located on the border between China and the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea, the Changbai Mountains are the highest mountain
range in the east of the Eurasian continent.
</P>
<P>
The Changbai Mountains Nature Reserve was established in 1960,
with the Heavenly Lake at its center. It covers an area of 196,465
ha. 
</P>
</TEXT>
