<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SOEs Must Start Making Profits in 3 Years: Jiang -1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin has
urged state-owned enterprises (SOE) in east China to start making
profits in three years' time by establishing a modern enterprise
system and optimizing the economic structure.
</P>
<P>
Establishing a modern enterprise system is a major issue which
has a vital bearing not only on the reform and development of the
SOEs but also on the success of the economic restructuring and the
sustainable and healthy development of the national economy in
China, the Chinese leader stressed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also general secretary of the Communist Party of
China Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military
Commission, made the remarks at a forum on reform and development
of SOEs in the six provinces and one municipality in east China,
in this scenic port city in Shandong Province Friday and today.
</P>
<P>
It was the fourth such forum the president called this year.
How to get the debt-ridden SOEs back into the black is the key
issue in China's development agenda, and the relatively developed
east China is spearheading the reform.
</P>
<P>
"State-owned enterprises must establish a management system
full of vitality to improve their competitiveness, and the modern
enterprise system is the basic enterprise system in a socialist
market economy," Jiang pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the establishment of a modern enterprise system
should center on clearly defined ownership, rights and
responsibilities, separation of government and enterprise
functions, and a scientific management system.
</P>
<P>
He expounded on the issue from eight aspects:
</P>
<P>
-- The respective rights and responsibilities of the state and
the enterprises should be clearly defined and understood, and SOEs
must set up an effective system to manage, supervise and operate
state assets;
</P>
<P>
-- Government should refrain from interfering in the operation
of enterprises, and separation of government and enterprise
functions should be achieved;
</P>
<P>
-- Large and medium-sized SOEs should be restructured into
standard corporations, while small SOEs should be granted more
flexibility in their operations. The legal person corporate
structure which guarantees a balance between owners and operators
is the core of the modern corporate system;
</P>
<P>
-- The building of enterprise leadership should be enhanced to
produce a highly qualified management contingent;
</P>
<P>
-- Scientific measures should be implemented to improve
management;
</P>
<P>
-- A reasonable distribution mechanism should be established to
give more incentives to both managers and workers;
</P>
<P>
-- Full reliance should be placed on staff to handle management.
The legal rights and interests of workers should be properly
protected, and special attention should be paid to laid-off
workers and those facing various kinds of difficulties; and
</P>
<P>
-- The leadership of the Party should be enhanced and improved.
And Party organizations should guarantee and supervise the
implementation of the Party and government policies in the
enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
