<HEADLINE> SOEs Must Start Making Profits in 3 Years: Jiang -2 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A relatively developed area endowed with a favorable
geographical position and the support of state policies, eastern
China has made rapid progress in reform and development, and made
great contributions to reform and development in the country as a
whole, the president noted.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the region should continue to deepen the
reform, promote the development of high- and new-technology
industries, to transform traditional industries with modern
science and technology, and to expand the opening-up and further
develop overseas markets.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Jiang pointed out, the east China area should
attach more importance to supporting the development of central
and western China by increasing trans-regional economic and
technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Central and western China, with their rich natural resources
and potential markets, will also help economic growth and social
progress in eastern China," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"Only by working for the common development of whole nation can
China achieve an overall rapid and coordinated economic
development," he added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also urged leading officials to improve their
ideological and theoretical standards and increase their sense of
responsibility in the course of the Party's current education in
theoretical study, political awareness and good conduct.
</P>
<P>
The president made a study tour of Shandong Province before
the forum, visiting local state-owned enterprises, some laid-off
workers, the traffic police, the armed police and the People's
Liberation Army units stationed in Shandong.  
</P>
