<HEADLINE> Guangxi Organizes Bicycle Trip to Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-six Chinese tourists today
began a unique trip into Vietnam by bicycle from Nanning, capital
of south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Their four-day sightseeing trip will cover 420 km, ending at
the Vietnamese capital city of Hanoi, according to the Nanning
Tourism Bureau, which organized the activity in coordination with
Vietnam's national tourism administration.
</P>
