<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0100 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Computers Cheaper, Simpler in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The TCL Group, one of China's
major household electric appliance suppliers, announced here this
weekend that it is to market a personal computer at half the price
of similar products next month.
</P>
<P>
The high-end PC is priced at 4,888 yuan (about 590 US dollars).
Yang Weiqiang, general manager of the TCL Computer Corporation,
under the TCL Group, said that the new household information
product poses a challenge to conventional high-end computers.
</P>
<P>
It has a unique hardware and software arrangement, combining
the functions of TV and computers. The new computer puts stress on
simplicity of use, according to Yang.
</P>
<P>
A large number of household electric appliance companies have
diversified their operations into PC manufacturing. They use their
financial strength and extensive networks of procurement and
distribution to compete with PC suppliers for market shares.
</P>
<P>
Though PC sales have reached 4.5 million annually in China, the
penetration rate of computers among households is only 1.7 percent,
much lower than the 55 percent in the United States.
</P>
<P>
The huge potential market has attracted giant electrical
appliance companies to the highly competitive PC arena.
</P>
<P>
Noting that these companies only entered the PC market two
years ago, and only account for around two percent of the total
sales of PCs in the country, Yang said that TCL will expand its
market share rapidly in the next two years.
</P>
<P>
Most of the electric appliance giants have gained access to
cheap supplies on the global procurement market by setting up
joint ventures with international companies.
</P>
<P>
TCL set up its computer corporation through a 125-million-yuan
joint venture with Taiwan-based GVC, the number four PC supplier
in the world.
</P>
<P>
It has also obtained billions of yuan in loans from Chinese
banks. With access to the cheapest components in the world and
abundant funding, the company is now able to market high-
performance computers at prices that are acceptable to the average
household in China.
</P>
<P>
In contrast, a similar computer produced by Legend, the largest
PC supplier in the country, are priced at around 1,000 US dollars.
Legend accounts for more than ten percent of the country's PC
market.
</P>
<P>
Yang said that it is still too early to say who will be the
winner in the competition. However, he believes that in the next
few years the gap between household electrical appliances and
computers will become much narrower, both in terms of prices and
functions.
</P>
<P>
Now the average prices of household electric appliances are
between 1,000 yuan and 4,000 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0101 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania Allows Unemployed Teachers to Work Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Though facing a shortage of
more than 20,000 teachers, Tanzania is forced to allow its
teachers unemployed due to financial difficulty to try to find job
abroad.
</P>
<P>
Juma Kapuya, Minister for Education and Culture, told the
parliament Friday that the government failed to employ all the
teachers because of its thin budget.
</P>
<P>
"Not that the government has become self sufficient in
teachers, but the economy doesn't allow to have them all
employed," he was quoted by local media Saturday as saying.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the ministry said the demand for teachers in
primary, secondary and teachers colleges stood at 129,687 as in
this month, while the existing teachers numbered 106,541, thus a
shortage of 23,146 teachers.
</P>
<P>
They said at least 21,212 teachers, 365 degree holders, 1,884
diplomas and 18,963 certificate teachers, remained unemployed by
June last year.
</P>
<P>
There are 18,059 unemployed teachers this year, however, the
government has given the ministry permission to employ only 1,890
of them for secondary schools and teachers colleges in 1999/2000
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The Minister said the unemployed teachers were free to seek
jobs in the private sector and outside the country.
</P>
<P>
"Those who secure employment outside the country will be
cleared by the ministry," Kapuya said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, a World Bank report said Tanzania is among
nine countries around the world with a primary school enrolment
rate of less than 50 percent.
</P>
<P>
The latest World Bank Poverty Update said Tanzania is only
ahead of Mozambique in sub-Saharan Africa where the world's lowest
enrolment rate is common.
</P>
<P>
The report said the lowest primary school enrolment rate is in
Niger where a mere 24.5 percent of school going children get
enrolled annually, while Tanzania has an enrolment rate of 47.8
percent.
</P>
<P>
Tanzanian government has decided to introduce education levy in
the country effective from October this year as a strategy to
improve the sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
