<HEADLINE> Barrichello Wins Pole Position for French Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Rubens Barrichello won the
pole position on Saturday when he topped the French Grand Prix
qualifying times in Magny-Cours.
</P>
<P>
World champion Mika Hakkinen qualified only 14th fastest in his
McLaren.
</P>
<P>
Barrichello set his time early in the session before the rain
intensified at the Magny-Cours circuit and he was able to retain
the best spot ahead of nearest rival Frenchman Jean Alesi.
</P>
