ironically on a day when Barrichello's former team Jordan saw one
of their drivers, 1996 world champion Damon Hill, fail to qualify.
</P>
<P>
Alesi, celebrating the 10th anniversary of his Formula One
debut at the 1989 French race, showed he had recovered from his
high-speed accident in practice on Friday and will start alongside
Barrichello.
</P>
<P>
Another Frenchman Olivier Panis qualified third in a Prost.
</P>
