<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: Pakistan for Just, Equitable Int'l Order: PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif said Saturday that his country calls for the establishment
of "a just and equitable international political and economic
order."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan, like China, is also of the view that the trend
towards multi-polarization is in the interest of world peace and
stability, Sharif said in an exclusive interview with a group of
Islamabad-based Chinese correspondents at the Prime Minister's
House.
</P>
<P>
"All our energies are therefore directed towards attaining the
ultimate goal of peace and development at home as well as outside,
and this will continue to be the prime objective of our foreign
policy in the years to come," said Sharif.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan, Sharif said, has emerged as "an independent,
non-aligned, democratic, progressive Islamic State", fully aware
of its responsibilities as a significant actor, both on the
international stage and at the regional level.
</P>
<P>
"And this is the position that I envisage for it at the
threshold of the 21st century," the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question about the development of the South Asian
Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC), Sharif said SAARC
has made "reasonable progress" in the last 14 years and has to
attain the level of mutual understanding that exists among members
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations or the European
Union.
</P>
<P>
"Unhappily, SAARC's forward march is inhibited by disputes and
disparities among its member states," said Sharif.
</P>
<P>
"There is an intrinsic link between peace and development,"
said Sharif, adding that "regional cooperation at the level of
SAARC can flourish only if an enabling environment of reliable
security and stability is put into place in South Asia."
</P>
<P>
Without that, the organization cannot be expected to flower and
bloom, Sharif noted.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated Pakistan's commitment to bringing about such an
environment for "promoting a regional process on security and
cooperation."
</P>
<P>
Sharif noted that for this purpose he presented to the SAARC
Summit in Colombo last year a Peace, Security and Development
Initiative.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister expressed the hope that his proposal will be
implemented by SAARC members in a sincere spirit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
