<HEADLINE> Injury Forces Johnson out of Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Double Olympic champion Michael
Johnson pulled out of the U.S. athletics championships in Eugene,
Oregon, on Friday after straining his right quadricep in training.
</P>
<P>
Johnson, the world 200-meter record-holder, had been scheduled
to meet world 100-meter record-holder Maurice Greene in the 200
meters on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The withdrawal means he can not run the event in the coming
world championships in Seveille, Spain in August, but as a wild
card can earn him a berth in the 400m competitions there since he
was the defending champion.
</P>
<P>
Clyde Hart, Johnson's coach, said Johnson could recover within
a few days or it may take several weeks. 
