caused the deaths of three people while 20 schools were closed
over fears of cattle-rustling.
</P>
<P>
Cattle-rustling is a rampant crime and a headache to the Kenyan
 government. In mid June, police chiefs from east African
countries considered it as one of four crimes which required top
priorities in the anti-crime operations. 
