<HEADLINE> New Granite Thoroughfare Paved In Downtown Beijing Commercial District </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The paving of a new granite-
surfaced thoroughfare was completed today in the reputed
Wangfujing Commercial District in downtown Beijing, and the road
has opened to traffic.
</P>
<P>
The main section of the new Wangfujing Avenue is 12m-wide and
810m-long, with its entire section paved with top-quality granite.
It took its road builders three months to complete the road.
</P>
<P>
Renowned as China's No.1 commercial street, the Wangfujing
Avenue is franked by large shopping centers and extravagant hotels.
The latest renovation project of this district started last year
and is expected to be completed by coming September. 
</P>
