the Caribbean and the European Union (EU) started the first pre-
summit meeting here Friday to look at the main documents and
topics on the summit agenda.
</P>
<P>
The main political document, "Declaration of Rio de Janeiro,"
is expected to be adopted by the two-day summit that concludes
next Tuesday. The Rio Summit is the first of its kind grouping
leaders or their representatives of 48 countries from the two
continents -- 33 from Latin America and the Caribbean, and 15 from
the EU. (LAmerica-EU-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
