<HEADLINE> EU Ready to Aid DRC After Ceasefire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Britain and other members of the
European Union are ready to offer assistance to the Democratic
Republic of Congo (DRC) as soon as a ceasefire agreement is
signed.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail newspaper Saturday quoted Diane Mckelvey,
second secretary at the British High Commission in Lusaka, as
saying: "the British government, European Union and others stand
ready to offer assistance to the people of the DRC as soon as
there is a ceasefire there that makes that possible."
</P>
<P>
Mckelvey also said the British government had been active in
assisting Zambia to cope with the influx of refugees from the DRC.
</P>
<P>
She said that the British High Commission Thomas Young visited
the refugee camp in Mporokoso, Zambia's Northern Province and
found the camp was well run and adequately funded.
</P>
<P>
Mckelvey said if there was a further influx of refugees, the
High Commission would consider what further assistance Britain
might give. 
