<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sex Knowledge Being Spread in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Knowledge about sex has been
considered part of the young people's basic cultural development,
and Beijing is promoting such knowledge through varied means.
</P>
<P>
Articles about sexual knowledge are now quite common in
magazines, and books such as Handbook of Sexual Knowledge are
available on almost every bookstand on the streets.
</P>
<P>
The TV program named Life and Childbirth, jointly made by the
city's family planning departments and the Beijing TV Station a
decade ago, has won widespread endorsement. Its main contents
cover reproduction health, and biology, including interviews with
professionals, lectures, knowledge contests, and telling stories
of daily life.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Telecommunications Bureau has also held
quizzes and offered hotline consultation on sex for more than a
decade.
</P>
<P>
Courses on sexual knowledge in many high schools in Beijing
have helped teenagers to form appropriate attitudes to love,
marriage and family life, which have been welcomed both by the
students and their parents.
</P>
<P>
Xiang Chunxiang, head of a publicity center of the family
planning program in Beijing, said that most of local residents are
now able to deal with sexually-related problems correctly and
properly thanks to scientific guidance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
