<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 06:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5 Tons of Narcotics Burned in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Marking the international anti-drug
day on Saturday, five tons of narcotics were burned in Iran's
central Kerman province on Friday, local daily Jomhuri Islami
reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Another 50 tons of drugs are to be burned in Tehran Saturday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Deputy secretary of the anti-drug headquarters at the Iranian
Presidential Office, who was only named as Heshmati, said at the
ceremony that the country allocates some 7,000 billion rials
(about 2.3 billion U.S. dollars) annually to fight against drug
trafficking.
</P>
<P>
He said some 270 Iranian anti-drug personnel have been killed
in anti-drug campaigns since the Islamic revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
The official put the number of addicts in Iran at 1 million,
adding that there are 210 million addicts throughout the world.
</P>
<P>
Iran launched large-scale anti-drug campaigns after the Iranian
Majlis (parliament) passed a strict anti-drug law in 1989 and the
number of confiscated narcotics increased drastically in recent
years, with 195 tons in 1998 alone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0159 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 06:58 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Drug Dealers Ordered to Leave UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A newly formed anti-drug
fieldwork team has ordered drug dealers to quit the United Arab
Emirates (UAE) or face dire consequences, the Gulf News daily
reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"If they fail to leave they will be handed over to overseas
authorities they are claimed by even if there is no extradition
treaty with that country," warned Dhahi Khalfan Tamim, police
chief of Dubai Emirate and head of the Fieldwork Team, which was
officially formed on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The major objective of the team is to knock out drug dealers
who spoiled the country's image by staying here, the police chief
said, adding that the team will issue administrative orders to
cancel their visas and deport them as well.
</P>
<P>
"Asking the drug dealers to leave the country is our present
to them on the occasion of the World Drug Fighting Day which
falls on June 26," Dhahi was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Intensive efforts to combat major drug dealers are being made
for the first time throughout the UAE. As a result, the Interior
Ministry decided to form the anti-drug team on April 28.
</P>
<P>
With the cooperation of anti-narcotics officers from various
emirates in the UAE, the team will try to follow up drug dealers
and stop all related activities in the next two years, according
to Dhahi, who will head the team for two years starting from
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that between 1995 and 1998, 15 tons of
narcotics were seized in the UAE, 80 percent of which was
hashish. During the same period, 8,607,717 hallucinatory pills
were also confiscated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
