<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0163 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes 41,000 Kilos of Drugs in 11 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized a
total of 41,011 kilos of narcotic drugs, including 4,301 kilos of
heroin, 29,037 kilos of opium and 6,728 kilos of marijuana, in the
11 years from 1988 to May 1999.
</P>
<P>
The authorities also seized 33,970 liters of phensedyl and
33.61 million tablets of stimulant drugs and punished 73,803
persons during the period.
</P>
<P>
The figures were disclosed here Saturday by Colonel Tin Hlaing,
Myanmar minister of home affairs, in his opening address on the
occasion of the International Day Against Drug Abuse and Illicit
Trafficking.
</P>
<P>
Colonel Tin Hlaing, who is also chairman of the Central
Committee for Drug Abuse Control, emphasized that the main
activities to realize the objectives of Myanmar in fighting
against narcotic drugs are the elimination of the cultivation of
opium poppy by improving the standard of living, developing the
cultivating areas and reducing the dependency on poppy cultivation
of the ethnic people living in the border areas.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the government has been implementing a 15-year
plan for opium eradication and implementation has been started in
the priority areas of 51 townships under five-year periods
beginning 1999-2000.
</P>
<P>
To assist in this work, a baseline data collection on poppy
cultivation and addicts has already been completed, he said.
</P>
<P>
Much money is needed to implement the said 15-year plan, he
said, adding that if international organizations help by providing
the necessary funds, the work can be completed in a shorter
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
