<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, June 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- The UK's economic output remained broadly flat during
the first three months of the year, according to official figures
released Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Office for National Statistics said while revised data
continued to show zero growth in the first quarter compared to the
last three months, year-on-year growth had been revised to 0.7
percent from a previous 0.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
It was the weakest performance for the economy since 1992.
However the figures did show the service sector performing more
strongly than had been thought. (UK-Economy)
</P>
<P>
