<HEADLINE> Polish Troops Depart for NATO Peacekeeping Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Some 150 Polish troops left for the
Balkans on Friday to take part in NATO's peacekeeping mission in
Kosovo, according to the Polish news agency.
</P>
<P>
The troops, which are the first batch of 800 Polish servicemen
to join NATO's Kosovo mission, will arrive in Macedonia first,
before entering Kosovo to implement peace in the U.S.-controlled
area.
</P>
<P>
The 800 servicemen, all from the well-armed and trained 18th
landing and assaulting battalion, will depart for Kosovo in groups
until next Tuesday, according to battalion commander Roman Polko.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that Poland will also send 100 policemen to
Kosovo at the request of the United Nations and the fifth group of
its medical team and fire-fighters will leave for Albania in early
July. 
</P>
</TEXT>
