<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Battles Misuse of Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The illegal occupation and rampant
misuse of land in China must be stopped, today's China Daily
quoted a senior legislator as saying Friday.
</P>
<P>
The statement was made at the ninth National Land Day which was
observed Friday with the theme "rationally using the land, and
acting in accordance with the law."
</P>
<P>
Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), said that the per capita amount
of arable land in the country is only 43 percent of world levels.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that most arable land in the country is rather poor
in quality.
</P>
<P>
More than half of China's 130 million hectares of arable land
is without irrigation, two-thirds of the farmland is not fertile,
and soil erosion affects nearly one-third of the land.
</P>
<P>
Jiang went on to say that the sustainable management and
protection of arable land is an important, but difficult
undertaking for the government.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that 414 people were punished in 1998 for
illegal land occupation or use.
</P>
<P>
More than 30 cases involving illegal land occupation or use
have been checked out by the Ministry of Land and Resources during
the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jiang said, the newly revised State Land Management
Law, which took effect early this year, should be strictly
enforced; arable land should be protected from illegal occupation
for non-agricultural use. Land rehabilitation work should be
carried out to improve the rural ecology and farm land's
productivity, he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
