<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka, Iraq Sign Accord on Culture, Science </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka and Iraq Friday signed
an accord on the implementation of a program on cultural and
scientific cooperation under the Cultural and Scientific Agreement
they signed in 1979, informed sources here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said this program is aimed at sharing and
furthering cultural and scientific links between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The new program will be effective from 2000 to 2002 and will
provide for exchange of scholarship, information and building up
cooperation in the field of sports.
</P>
<P>
Cultural and scientific links are an important area in
diplomatic relations and Sri Lanka is looking forward to making
use of these opportunities for the benefit of the people of both
countries, once the agreement is implemented early next year, the
sources quoted a Foreign Ministry director here as saying.
</P>
<P>
An agreement on economic and technical cooperation was signed
by the two countries last Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
