<HEADLINE> Mexico, ALADI To Sign Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Mexico and the Latin American
Integration Association (ALADI) will sign a cooperation agreement
during the official visit of Mexican President Ernesto Zedillo to
Uruguay, according to ALADI sources.
</P>
<P>
The agreement aims at jointly implementing projects of
technical cooperation in areas of common interest to benefit less
developed economies.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican president's visit to the ALADI headquarters in
Montevideo will be regarded as a demonstration of his country's
support for the integration process promoted by the regional
institution.
</P>
<P>
The ALADI Representatives Committee will hold an extraordinary
session to honor the Mexican president, who will attend it
accompanied by Foreign Minister Rosario Green and Trade and
Industrial Promotion Minister Herminio Blanco.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Green and ALADI General Secretary Juan F.
Rojas will sign the cooperation agreement at the end of the
session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
