<HEADLINE> EDS-Urgent Talks between DPRK, ROK Resume in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 26 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's Republic
of Korea (DPRK) and the Republic of Korea (ROK) resumed their vice-
ministerial talks in a Beijing hotel this morning after three days
of suspension.
</P>
<P>
Yang Young-Sik, vice-minister of ROK National Unification, and
Pak Yong-Su, vice-director-general of the DPRK Committee for
Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland, greeted each other as
the talks began.
</P>
<P>
The two sides held one and a half hours of talks last Tuesday,
in which they discussed a number of issues including the reunion
of separated families, the implementation of an accord signed in
1991 on reconciliation, mutual non-aggression and cooperation
between the north and the south, and the recent skirmishes
involving the two navies in a disputed area of the Yellow Sea.
</P>
<P>
At press time, the talks are still going on. 
</P>
</TEXT>
