<HEADLINE> Coetzer Becomes Fifth Seed Victim at Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Amanda Coetzer of South Africa
became the fifth seed victim as she was beaten by Belgian teenager
Kim Clijsters in straight sets at the Wimbledon on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 12th seed was outscored by 16-year-old qualifier Clijsters
6-2, 6-4 in the third round, a perfect blessing for Steffi Graf as
the German veteran will clash against the Belgian in the last
eight.
</P>
<P>
Clijsters, who ranked 195th in the world, was only making her
main draw debut this year after finishing runner-up in the juniors
event in 1998.
</P>
<P>
However, Coetzer also became the second South African player to
be beaten by the Belgian who eliminated Joannette Kruger by
straight sets in the first round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
