<HEADLINE> WB Grants 3 Loans to Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank has approved three
loans totaling 134 million U.S. dollars to boost economic
development in Bosnia, the Croatian TV station reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
A loan of 50 million dollars will be utilized to help Bosnia
privatize its enterprises and banks. The second loan of 12 million
dollars will be used to promote  export industries while the
third of 72 million will help improve the financial situation in
the Balkan country.
</P>
<P>
Observers say the purposes of the loans indicate that the World
Bank's assistance for the Bosnian government has advanced from the
phase of economic restoration to that of economic development.
</P>
</TEXT>
