<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Croatian Teenager Topples Monica Seles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Croatian 17-year-old Mirjana Lucic
scored her biggest victory by toppling fourth-seeded former
finalist Monica Seles in two tiebrekers, sailing to the last eight
at the Wimbledon tournament on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Lucic who ranked 134th in the world, stunned Seles who won all
Grand Slam titles except Wimbledon, by winning the tiebreakers 7-6
(7/4), 7-6 (7/4) in nearly 100 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Seles, 25, a finalist in 1992, lost her golden chance to
establish a 4-2 lead in the opening set when she held a triple
break point as Lukic saved all three and held for 3-3.
</P>
<P>
After forcing the first tiebreak with an ace, the tall Croatian
promptly surged into a 6-2 lead before wrapping it up on her third
set point.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, Seles, who has nine Grand Slam singles
titles to her name, broke first in the seventh game for a 4-3 lead,
only to be clawed back in the next game for a 4-all deadlock.
</P>
<P>
With all pressure upon herself, Seles came within two points of
defeat before holding for 5-5 and squandering her two break points
to allow Lucic a 6-5 lead.
</P>
<P>
Seles served an ace to force another tiebreak which saw Lucic
moved from 2-0 to 4-2 and 5-4 before the Croatian putting away
with a backhand volley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Volkswagen Developing New Models </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai Volkswagen, China's
leading car producer, is now busy developing new models in order
to maintain its superior status amid increasing market competition.
</P>
<P>
One of them, according to the corporation's general manager
Hong Jiming, is the Passat, a sedan car based on the overseas
Passat B5. It is able to reach a top speed of 206 km per hour at
times but can travel approximately one hundred kilometers on only
5.8 liters of gasoline.
</P>
<P>
Mass production of the Passat is to commence next March and its
sales price will be around 220,000 to 250,000 yuan (26,500 to 30,
000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Another model, an economy car targeting Chinese families, will
be available in two to three years. Its price will be pegged at
around 100,000 yuan (12,000 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Volkswagen was jointly established by Germany's
Volkswagen and the Shanghai Automotive Industry Corporation in
1984, and has since manufactured more than 1.2 million Santana
cars. It has a 46 percent share of the Chinese car market.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture is currently building a technological
development center and a special car test ground that will be
operational within this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
