<DOCNO> XIE19990626.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Reports Falling May Price Indexes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 26 (Xinhua)-- The May retail price index for
south China's Guangdong Province fell 4.7 percent on last year's
same period, with the consumer price index for the period falling
3.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The provincial statistics bureau reported that food prices
dropped by 2.8 percent on April levels and by 7.6 percent on last
year's period.
</P>
<P>
Food grain, meat, poultry, eggs, fruits and vegetables fell by
lesser degrees.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, prices for clothing, jewelry, textiles, cosmetics,
machinery and electronic products also dropped.
</P>
<P>
Prices for service items were up 0.6 percent on April and 5.6
percent on the same month last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
