<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU President Arrives in Brazil for Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- European Union President
Jacques Santer arrived in Rio de Janeiro on Friday morning for the
summit with Latin America and the Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
Santer's retinue is formed by 18 high-ranking EU officials, who
will meet with their Latin American counterparts at the Modern Art
Museum of this city.
</P>
<P>
A total of 48 heads of state and government or their
representatives -- 33 from Latin America and 15 from the EU --
will be present at the summit scheduled for next Monday and
Tuesday, following the meeting of the foreign ministers on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of the summit includes free trade between the EU and
the Southern Common Market (Mercosur), joint war against drug
trafficking, cooperation on environment protection as well as
political, economic and social issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
