<HEADLINE> Goalie Germano Leaves Brazilian National Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Goalkeeper Carlos Germano
became the third player within one week to leave the Brazilian
national squad on Friday as the team is preparing for the Copa
America tournament.
</P>
<P>
Germano was forced out by a knee injury and will be replaced by
Palmeiras' Marcos, said Vitor Oliver, a spokesman for the
Brazilian Soccer Federation.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, midfielder Leonardo of AC Milan, left the squad
after he failed to be named captain of the team.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, coach Wanderely Luxemburgo kicked out Edilson of
Corinthians after he provoked players from rivals Palmeiras by
ball juggling while his team coasted to victory in the Sao Paulo
state final.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian team will play Venezuela on June 30 to start its
journey along the Copa America tournament. 
</P>
