<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Down Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange on
Friday closed down for the fourth day, with the benchmark IPC
index reducing by 33.94 points, or 0.61 percent, at 5,515.24
points from 5,549.18 on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Operators exchanged 59.353 million shares for an amount of some
71.534 million dollars against 94.005 million shars worth 132.810
million dollars on the previous day.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood at 9.65 to one dollar for
sale and 9.30 for purchase in the main exchange houses of the
Mexico City, compared with 9.60 for sale and 9.30 for purchase on
Thursday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
