<HEADLINE> Argentine Stock Indes Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index of
the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange closed down 0.85 percent at 535.80
points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover reached only 31.690 million dollars compared with
39.304 million U.S. dollars on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The annual interbank rate of interest maintained 7.10 percent
in the 24-hour term and the peso parity against the dollar
remained unchanged at 0.997 for purchase and 1.002 for sale.
