<HEADLINE> Lhasa Establishes Links to Information Highway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 26 (Xinhua) -- Lhasa, the capital of the Tibet
Autonomous Region, is now linked to the national information
highway thanks to assistance provided by scientists from east
China's Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from Jiangsu helped the Municipal Science and
Technology Bureau establish the Lhasa Science and Technology
Information Center which features advanced hardware and software.
</P>
<P>
Local companies, institutions and individuals can access the
Internet and a number of science and technology information
centers throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The Lhasa city government is also developing scientific
achievements and market information databases.
</P>
<P>
The central government has named 1999 as the year governments
at all levels will gain access to the Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
