<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Boosts Software Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 26 (Xinhua) -- A software park has been inaugurated
at the Xi'an New and High-tech Development Zone.
</P>
<P>
This marks the start of a rapid growth for the software
industry in this capital of northwest China's Shaanxi Province,
said a local government official.
</P>
<P>
The project was divided into two phases, and the first phase
has already gone into partial operation, with more than 30
information enterprises operational. The overall plan for the
second phase is now off the drawing board.
</P>
<P>
Xi'an enjoys exceptional advantages for software development.
More than 6,000 B.A. and M.A. students majoring in computer
science graduate from over 40 universities and colleges in Shaanxi
annually, serving as a large reserve force for software research.
</P>
<P>
At present, Xi'an has a total of 500 software companies and
research institutes, with approximately 30,000 staff members.
Their combined annual business turnover exceeded one billion yuan
(120 million US dollars) last year, up 150 percent over the figure
for the previous year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
