<HEADLINE> Seles Becomes Casualty on Day 5 of Wimbledon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles once again failed to
realize her dream of Wimbledon tennis title when the American
fourth seed lost to Croatian Mirjana Lucic 7-6, 7-6 in the third
round on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Seles has won at all other three Grand Slams of Australian Open,
French Open and U.S. Open, but the Wimbledon is the only one that
elude her.
</P>
<P>
The American player was one of three top women to fall by the
wayside as 13th seed Sandrine Testud of France lost 6-2, 1-6, 6-3
to Tamarine Tanasugarn of Thailand and South Africa's Amanda
Coetzer, seeded 12, went down 6-2, 6-4 to 16-year-old Kim
Clijsters.
</P>
<P>
However, second seed Steffi Graf brushed aside American Corina
Morariu 6-1, 6-3 while Venus Williams, last year's finalist
Nathalie Tauziat and Anna Kournikova also scored easy wins.
</P>
<P>
Graf, the French Open champion, said she felt good about the
way she was playing but was taking nothing for granted.
</P>
<P>
"There's still so many good players out there," she said.
</P>
<P>
Williams, seeded sixth, dropped just two games against Sarah
Pitkowski of France as did Tauziat of France against Seda
Noorlander of the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Williams now plays 17th seed Kournikova after injury forced
Ines Gorrochategui of Argentina to retire with the Russian leading
7-5, 3-1.
</P>
<P>
"I'm improving all the time and I've found my rhythm," said
Kournikova. "Grass is not her (Williams's) favourite surface but
she's still got a big serve and I will have to outthink her and
play smarter."
</P>
<P>
Williams was looking forward to the match. "Me and Anna are a
great match-up. She's likes the grass and I know she'll get lots
of support from the British crowd, but that doesn't bother me. She
's got lots of strengths, but so have I."
</P>
<P>
Clijsters, the youngest women in the singles draw, was the
runner-up in the Wimbledon junior event last year and has yet to
drop a set in her senior debut in a Grand Slam tournament.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
