<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Police Bust Bank Fraud Ring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 25 (Xinhua) -- Police in Italian north city of Milan
Friday busted a gang specialized in bank fraud and arrested four
people, a fifth is still at large, believed to had taken upwards
of 10 billion lire (about 5.5 million U.S. dollars) from seven
banks and some 300 companies.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said the gang set up fake companies that were
given significant credit lines from the banks. When they reached
the maximum amount of their overdraft, the company would simply
disappear.
</P>
<P>
The 300 companies which were defrauded sold merchandise to the
fake companies but never received payment. Several of the 300
companies went bankrupt because of this.
</P>
<P>
The investigation which led to Friday's arrests began after
police in January 1998 seized a container that had arrived from
the United States with 7 tons of contraband cigarettes, valued at
over 2 billion lire (about 1.1 million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
