<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia Closes Army Press Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 25 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav military announced
on Friday the closure of its war-time press center after it had
completed the war-time work.
</P>
<P>
An international press center will take over from the army
press center for the coverage of post-war reconstruction of the
Balkan country, the military command said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
With 2,510 journalists accredited, the army press center
organized 39 collective field trips and some 2,000 individual
trips during the weeks of NATO air strikes.
</P>
<P>
Set up in end March, the army press center held 25 news
conferences for journalists coming from both abroad and home.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,535 journalists from foreign mass media
institutions got assistance from the army press center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
